## `select()`

::: columns
::: {.column width="38%"}
#### Subset variables

- by name  
- by position  
- by type  
:::

::: {.column width="62%"}
::: {.med-code}

::: {.cell hash='evolmar-tidyverse_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-8_0ad09d10450a1a00c4f96d297772502c'}

```{.r .cell-code}
sneakers %>% 
  select(Name, Sport) %>% 
  head(4)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
# A tibble: 4 √ó 2
  Name       Sport   
  <chr>      <chr>   
1 Boost 3000 Running 
2 HiSpeed    Running 
3 Super2     Trail   
4 Goal       Football
```
:::
:::

:::
:::
:::

## `mutate()`

::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}

#### Create and modify columns

- create new  
- overwrite  
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}

::: {.cell hash='evolmar-tidyverse_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-9_6a02bfc494d62a88d212854fc020e874'}

```{.r .cell-code}
sneakers %>%
  select(Name, Rating) %>% 
  mutate(Rating= Rating*2) %>% 
  head(5)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
# A tibble: 5 √ó 2
  Name       Rating
  <chr>       <dbl>
1 Boost 3000      8
2 HiSpeed         8
3 Super2         10
4 Goal            6
5 Goal2.0         8
```
:::
:::

:::
:::

We can control where the new column will appear with `.before` and `.after`


## `filter()`

::: columns
::: {.column width="48%"}

#### Subset rows

- keep rows that meet a condition
:::

::: {.column width="52%"}

::: {.cell hash='evolmar-tidyverse_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-10_cc6dd17503d6be3109a9fea6cdd0e9ba'}

```{.r .cell-code}
sneakers %>% 
  select(Name, Sport, Rating) %>% 
  filter(Rating == 5)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
# A tibble: 3 √ó 3
  Name         Sport   Rating
  <chr>        <chr>    <int>
1 Super2       Trail        5
2 Glide Best   Running      5
3 Outdoor King Trail        5
```
:::
:::


:::
:::

> `filter()` always needs a logical vector to keep/discard rows


::: {.cell hash='evolmar-tidyverse_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-11_9bd9bec5d87b1a7606becc0bb2827518'}

```{.r .cell-code}
sneakers$Rating == 5
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
 [1] FALSE FALSE  TRUE FALSE FALSE FALSE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE FALSE FALSE
```
:::
